Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.store

Interface RecordStore<RECORD extends AbstractBaseRecord>

  • Type Parameters:
    RECORD - type of AbstractBaseRecord.
    All Superinterfaces:
    IdSequence
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDynamicStore, AccessStatsKeepingStoreAccess.AccessStatsKeepingRecordStore, CommonAbstractStore, DynamicArrayStore, DynamicStringStore, LabelTokenStore, MetaDataStore, NodeStore, PropertyKeyTokenStore, PropertyStore, RecordStore.Delegator, RelationshipGroupStore, RelationshipStore, RelationshipTypeTokenStore, SchemaStore, SchemaStore35, TokenStore
    public interface RecordStore<RECORD extends AbstractBaseRecord>
extends IdSequence
    A store for updating and getRecord(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursorTracer) getting} records. There are two ways of getting records, either one-by-one using getRecord(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursorTracer), passing in record retrieved from newRecord(). This to make a conscious decision about who will create the record instance and in that process figure out ways to reduce number of record instances created.

    The other way is to use openPageCursorForReading(long, PageCursorTracer) to open a cursor and use it to read records using getRecordByCursor(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursor). A PageCursor can be ket open to read multiple records before closing it.

      • setHighestPossibleIdInUse

        void setHighestPossibleIdInUse​(long highestIdInUse)
        Sets highest id in use for this store. This is for when records are applied to this store where the ids have been generated through some other means. Having an up to date highest possible id makes sure that closing this store truncates at the right place and that "all record scans" can see all records.
        Parameters:

      • getRecord

        RECORD getRecord​(long id,
                 RECORD target,
                 RecordLoad mode,
                 PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
          throws InvalidRecordException
        Reads a record from the store into target. Depending on RecordLoad given there will be different behavior, although the target record will be marked with the specified id after participating in this method call.
        • RecordLoad.CHECK: As little data as possible is read to determine whether the record is in use or not. If not in use then no more data will be loaded into the target record and the data of the record will be cleared.
        • RecordLoad.NORMAL: Just like RecordLoad.CHECK, but with the difference that an InvalidRecordException will be thrown if the record isn't in use.
        • RecordLoad.FORCE: The entire contents of the record will be loaded into the target record regardless if the record is in use or not. This leaves no guarantees about the data in the record after this method call, except that the id will be the specified id.
        • RecordLoad.ALWAYS: Similar to RecordLoad.FORCE, except the sanity checks on the record data is always enabled.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the record to load.
        target - record where data will be loaded into. This record will have its id set to the specified id as part of this method call.
        mode - loading behaviour, read more in method description.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer.
        Returns:
        the record that was passed in, for convenience.
        Throws:
        InvalidRecordException - if record not in use and the mode allows for throwing.

      • getRecordByCursor

        void getRecordByCursor​(long id,
                       RECORD target,
                       RecordLoad mode,
                       PageCursor cursor)
                throws InvalidRecordException
        Reads a record from the store into target, see getRecord(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursorTracer).

        The provided page cursor will be used to get the record, and in doing this it will be redirected to the correct page if needed.

        Parameters:
        id - the record id, understood to be the absolute reference to the store.
        target - the record to fill.
        mode - loading behaviour, read more in getRecord(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursorTracer).
        cursor - the PageCursor to use for record loading.
        Throws:
        InvalidRecordException - if record not in use and the mode allows for throwing.

      • nextRecordByCursor

        void nextRecordByCursor​(RECORD target,
                        RecordLoad mode,
                        PageCursor cursor)
                 throws InvalidRecordException
        Reads a record from the store into target, see getRecord(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursorTracer).

        This method requires that the cursor page and offset point to the first byte of the record in target on calling. The provided page cursor will be used to get the record, and in doing this it will be redirected to the next page if the input record was the last on it's page.

        Parameters:
        target - the record to fill.
        mode - loading behaviour, read more in getRecord(long, AbstractBaseRecord, RecordLoad, PageCursorTracer).
        cursor - the PageCursor to use for record loading.
        Throws:
        InvalidRecordException - if record not in use and the mode allows for throwing.

      • ensureHeavy

        void ensureHeavy​(RECORD record,
                 PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        For stores that have other stores coupled underneath, the "top level" record will have a flag saying whether or not it's light. Light means that no records from the coupled store have been loaded yet. This method can load those records and enrich the target record with those, marking it as heavy.
        Parameters:
        record - record to make heavy, if not already.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer.

      • getRecords

        List<RECORD> getRecords​(long firstId,
                        RecordLoad mode,
                        boolean guardForCycles,
                        PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
                 throws InvalidRecordException
        Reads records that belong together, a chain of records that as a whole forms the entirety of a data item.
        Parameters:
        firstId - record id of the first record to start loading from.
        mode - RecordLoad mode.
        guardForCycles - Set to true if we need to take extra care in guarding for cycles in the chain. When a cycle is found, a RecordChainCycleDetectedException will be thrown. If false, then chain cycles will likely end up causing an OutOfMemoryError. A cycle would only occur if the store is inconsistent, though.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer
        Returns:
        Collection of records in the loaded chain.
        Throws:
        InvalidRecordException - if some record not in use and the mode is allows for throwing.

      • streamRecords

        void streamRecords​(long firstId,
                   RecordLoad mode,
                   boolean guardForCycles,
                   PageCursorTracer cursorTracer,
                   RecordSubscriber<RECORD> subscriber)
        Streams records that belong together, a chain of records that as a whole forms the entirety of a data item.
        Parameters:
        firstId - record id of the first record to start loading from.
        mode - RecordLoad mode.
        guardForCycles - Set to true if we need to take extra care in guarding for cycles in the chain. When a cycle is found, a RecordChainCycleDetectedException will be thrown. If false, then chain cycles will likely end up causing an OutOfMemoryError. A cycle would only occur if the store is inconsistent, though.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer
        subscriber - The subscriber of the data, will receive records until the subscriber returns false

      • getNumberOfReservedLowIds

        int getNumberOfReservedLowIds()
        Some stores may have meta data stored in the header of the store file. Since all records in a store are of the same size the means of storing that meta data is to occupy one or more records at the beginning of the store (0...).
        Returns:
        the number of records in the beginning of the file that are reserved for header meta data.

      • getStoreHeaderInt

        int getStoreHeaderInt()
        Returns store header (see getNumberOfReservedLowIds()) as int. Exposed like this for convenience since all known store headers are ints.
        Returns:
        store header as an int value, e.g the first 4 bytes of the first (reserved) record in this store.

      • scanAllRecords

        <EXCEPTION extends Exception> void scanAllRecords​(Visitor<RECORD,​EXCEPTION> visitor,
                                                  PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
                                           throws EXCEPTION extends Exception
        Scan the given range of records both inclusive, and pass all the in-use ones to the given processor, one by one. The record passed to the NodeRecordScanner is reused instead of reallocated for every record, so it must be cloned if you want to save it for later.
        Parameters:
        visitor - Visitor notified about all records.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer.
        Throws:
        EXCEPTION - on error reading from store.
        EXCEPTION extends Exception
